# ============================================================
# .env  —  Parliament Scraper Configuration
# Copy from .env.example, fill in real values, never commit
# ============================================================

# ── GitHub Upload Token ──────────────────────────────────────
# What:    Personal Access Token to push PDFs to storage repo
# How:     github.com → Settings → Developer settings →
#          Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic) →
#          Generate new token → scope: repo
# Looks like: ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# ── PDF Storage Repository ───────────────────────────────────
# What:    The GitHub repo where PDFs will be pushed daily
# How:     Create a new empty repo on GitHub e.g.
#          github.com/new  →  name it "parliament-pdfs"
#          Then use the format owner/repo-name
# Example: myusername/parliament-pdfs
PDF_STORAGE_REPO=YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/parliament-pdfs

# ── Output Directory ─────────────────────────────────────────
# What:    Local folder where PDFs are saved (auto-created)
#          Year subfolders are created automatically inside:
#          debates/2023/, debates/2024/, debates/2025/ etc.
# How:     Just set a folder name — no action needed
OUTPUT_DIR=debates